	   <tr><td colspan=2>While bards are a great addition to any group, they can solo better than most classes in the game. Since many people know very little about bards, I'll be nice and lay out a few techniques.<br><br>First, you have to remember that a soloing bard has little or zero down time. With the exception of a few songs, bards do not use mana. Pick any three songs and a talented bard can used them indefinitely. Even if it takes you 4 or 5 minutes to kill a mob, you're still killing it in about the same amount of time that it takes a soloing casting to kill and med. Now on to the techniques.<br><br>Level 12: At level 12 you get your first dd song. Most look at the damage it does and laugh, but when you twist this with selos you can dd for 2 ticks then speed for one. This technique will be effective for the rest of your characters life versus non casting mobs up to 4(can go higher if you're desperate) levels higher than you.<br><br>Level 23: Now you have snare. This doesn't really change things at this level, but snare will be needed for future techniques and can also(although risky) allow you to kite in smaller areas when needed.<br><br>Level 26: Fear. Yet another dangerous technique, but as any necro will tell fear kiting is a very effective.<br><br>Level 27: Charm. Your life will never be the same. Charm does not cost any mana until this song becomes obsolete in the upper thirties. I have cleared the entire aviak house in south k (all except for top level) using charm. What level you ask? 29.<br><br>Level 28: Mezz. Although there isn't technique that really uses this song, it will help when breaking apart multiple mobs and makes life on the bard easier.<br><br>Level 30: Target DoT. This really helps the kiting go faster. If you're lucky enough to get your hands on a MM drum, this song can cut the time it takes to kite in half at least.<br><br>Level 32: Mana song. We're talking about soloing so need to give anyone else mana =)<br><br>My bard is only level 35 so the rest will be based on research, not personal experience.<br><br>Level 38: Yet another target DoT. Kiting continues.<br><br>Level 39: New Charm. This one takes mana but can still be very useful. Hats off to Soeb of Luclin. When we did Naggy raids, I've witnessed him keep as many as 3 giants occupied while the other 20+ people focused on killing one.<br><br>Level 46: Yet another target DoT. See a pattern?<br><br>Hope this helped some of you to understand a little bit more about your local bard.<br><br>-Anon Bard from Tholuxe<br><br>Oh yea, and next time your in a group with a bard, don't tell them to just play mana/heal song(depending on level). We really hate that =(<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
